<div id="c2936">

<p>Ha, it&#8217;s a small world!</p>

<p>My former college roommate studied economics at Stanford before deciding that Sociology was a better fit for him. He became good friends with Granovetter, and thinks the world of him. Now, I&#8217;ve never met the guy, but it might not be a bad idea to introduce yourself. If you want to seed the conversation, you can say you know a guy who knows the Angry Nihilist Former-Economics Grad Student Steve. I&#8217;ll bet he knows exactly who you are talking about.</p>

<p>For what it&#8217;s worth, my buddy Steve&#8217;s blog is available online at http://www.livejournal.com/users/ppaladin123/. If you&#8217;re interested in getting to know Granovetter, drop him a line at his blog and I&#8217;m sure he could tell you some useful stuff. At the moment, he&#8217;s teaching English in Japan, so any questions will probably be gratefully answered. (He seems bored out of his mind.)</p>

<p class="posted">posted by <a target="_blank" title="http://www.aetherial.net" href="http://notabug.com/mt/gorsnikat.cgi?__mode=red;id=2936">Chris</a> at September 28, 2004 10:30 PM <a href="001426#c2936">#</a></p>

